00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:29,570
It wasn't until noon
that Lynette finally took a break,

466
00:37:29,647 --> 00:37:34,675
and the reality of what she had done
began to sink in.

467
00:37:34,785 --> 00:37:37,549
My. What big eyes you have.

468
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:46,186
I'm going to the store.
Do you need anything?

469
00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:48,891
I'm fine, thank you.

470
00:37:50,701 --> 00:37:54,102
So what's been going on with her?
Have you found anything out yet?

471
00:37:54,171 --> 00:38:00,735
Actually, the more I watch her, the more
I think she's not stepping out on you.

472
00:38:00,811 --> 00:38:04,975
- Really?
- Yeah. She's not perfect, Lord knows.

473
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:08,450
But she loves you. I can tell.

474
00:38:08,586 --> 00:38:10,520
[Sighs]

475
00:38:10,621 --> 00:38:14,523
Mama. You don't know what a relief it is
to hear that.

476
00:38:16,927 --> 00:38:20,522
You know, it's funny.
I really think she loves you, too.

477
00:38:20,598 --> 00:38:22,725
Oh?

478
00:38:24,802 --> 00:38:28,704
I got concerned when I heard
you played poker with her friends.

479
00:38:29,940 --> 00:38:32,966
So I told her about your little problem.

480
00:38:35,646 --> 00:38:38,547
You told her about my gambling problem?

481
00:38:38,649 --> 00:38:42,312
Don't be mad. I just didn't want you
slipping into old habits.

482
00:38:42,386 --> 00:38:46,948
- She was very concerned about you.
- She knew?

483
00:38:51,796 --> 00:38:57,428
I don't get it. You and Zach never
went to school with anybody named Dana.

484
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:59,492
He didn't say
we went to school with her.

485
00:38:59,570 --> 00:39:03,939
- Did it sound like a relative?
- It sounded like "Dana".

486
00:39:04,008 --> 00:39:07,034
Unless he was using a code,
that's all I got.

487
00:39:07,111 --> 00:39:11,275
OK, give me a break here.
I'm just grasping at straws.

488
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:16,878
I'm sorry. I'm worried about Zach.
It's really creepy in there.

489
00:39:16,987 --> 00:39:20,582
- Can't we get him out?
- Honey, that's up to his father.

490
00:39:23,227 --> 00:39:26,287
- Then I want to visit again.
- That's not a good idea either.

491
00:39:26,397 --> 00:39:28,797
Why?

492
00:39:30,868 --> 00:39:33,598
I just have a feeling.

493
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:45,713
Juanita was now
more convinced than ever

494
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:49,275
that her treacherous
daughter-in-law was having an affair.

495
00:39:49,353 --> 00:39:52,948
But the question remained, with whom?

496
00:40:06,771 --> 00:40:09,501
And suddenly...

497
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:14,100
Juanita remembered
it wasn't the men Gabrielle talked to

498
00:40:14,211 --> 00:40:16,270
that she had to worry about.

499
00:40:21,652 --> 00:40:26,589
Hey, Jordana, Maisy.
Here are the costumes. Right on time.

500
00:40:26,657 --> 00:40:29,285
Thank you, Lynette.

501
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:36,556
This is a bit awkward. There has been
an oversight with the programs.

502
00:40:36,667 --> 00:40:40,000
Celia Bond is still credited
with costumes.

503
00:40:40,104 --> 00:40:43,164
They forgot to tell the printer.

504
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:45,265
Uh-huh.

505
00:40:45,342 --> 00:40:50,109
Who is "they", as in,
"they forgot to tell the printer"?

506
00:40:51,782 --> 00:40:55,809
That would be me. I'm sorry.

507
00:40:55,886 --> 00:41:00,255
But I was so overworked this week with
all the script changes you demanded.

508
00:41:00,357 --> 00:41:02,882
Uh-huh. Well, these things happen.

509
00:41:05,596 --> 00:41:07,564
Be right back.

510
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:12,400
Would you do something with this?
It looks like road kill.

511
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:17,839
OK, lady, that's it.

512
00:41:19,710 --> 00:41:22,235
- I beg your pardon?
- We have kids the same age.

513
00:41:22,346 --> 00:41:25,577
There are years ahead of us
having to deal with each other.

514
00:41:25,683 --> 00:41:29,779
So instead of playing petty games, why
don't we put an end to this right now?

515
00:41:29,854 --> 00:41:33,722
- What are you saying?
- Let's take it outside.

516
00:41:33,791 --> 00:41:37,352
- Let's take what outside?
- Your sorry ass. We're throwin' down.

517
00:41:37,428 --> 00:41:40,226
- You are crazy.
- Just being practical.

518
00:41:40,297 --> 00:41:42,094
Isn't it better to settle this

519
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:44,532
rather than endure
all this alpha-mom crap

520
00:41:44,635 --> 00:41:47,160
until our kids graduate?

521
00:41:47,238 --> 00:41:50,332
Come on.
I'll even let you take the first shot.

522
00:42:00,784 --> 00:42:03,810
- I don't have time for this.
- Yeah, I didn't think so.

523
00:42:03,921 --> 00:42:07,618
And just so you know,
next spring, when we do Bambi,

524
00:42:07,725 --> 00:42:12,389
his mother's gonna take a slug
to the heart and you're gonna like it.

525
00:42:20,938 --> 00:42:24,704
The search for power begins
when we're quite young.

526
00:42:24,775 --> 00:42:30,975
As children, we're taught that the power
of good triumphs over the power of evil.

527
00:42:31,048 --> 00:42:37,578
But as we get older, we realize
that nothing is ever that simple.

528
00:42:37,688 --> 00:42:41,522
Traces of evil always remain.

